dcterms:description: The CIFAR-10 dataset consists of 60000 RGB images in 10 classes, with 6000 images per class. It is commonly used for training machine learning models in image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-10

dcterms:creator: A. Krizhevsky
G. Hinton
dcterms:description: The CIFAR-100 dataset is similar to CIFAR-10 but contains 100 classes with 600 images each. It is used for more fine-grained image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-100

dcterms:description: The two-moon dataset is a synthetic dataset used for binary classification tasks, characterized by two interleaving half circles. It is often used to test clustering and classification algorithms.
dcterms:title: Two-moon dataset
